<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A 4.5-magnitude earthquake has rocked Southern California, with tremors felt from Los Angeles down to San Diego. </p>

<p>The quake hit 10 miles west of L.A. at 11.39 pm local time on Friday, according to the US Geological Survey. </p>

<p>It occurred at depth of nearly 11 miles, and lasted for 30 seconds. It was reported to be one of the biggest earthquakes to hit the L.A. area in years. </p>

<p>There have been no reports of injuries or damage to property, but authorities warned locals to prepare for aftershocks.  </p>

<p>It comes amid fears a large earthquake could rock the region  </p>

